We are a studio of diverse styles, voices and views reflecting the diversity of our customers, and giving us the empathy to serve their needs. Nurturing and continuously evolving this culture are our shared responsibility, because we create better products together. We believe designing in the open empowers us all to move fast and build experiences without seams. 
We share, we jam, we collaborate. We re-use rather than reinvent. We contribute to each otherâ€™s work to make it better. We work in small, cross-app, interdisciplinary teams to ensure we build experiences that are inclusive, efcient and delightful. 
We make to think, we prototype and test. We build both category-leading apps, and seamlessly connected experiences across them. 
We tell compelling emotional stories to open space for innovation, win new customers and take our existing customers along. We push boundaries constantly because we believe in the magic of bold ideas. And because itâ€™s our responsibility to strive to be best-in-class. We owe it to our company, and our customers. 
Ethically reducing time to value leveraging insights through big data is arguably a significant challenge for enterprises today. Dynamics 365 Customer Insights has been building momentum in this space and has become a market leader in several categories. As part of our evolution, we are innovating at a rapid pace, designing new experiences that extend from convergence of privacy-first and identified data. If you are curious and have a passion for complexity, come join our multidisciplinary team of designers and UX researchers who are transforming the workplace. 
The AI + Insights Studio is looking for a passionate and focused Product Designer with an exceptional eye for craftspersonship. As we continue to expand our team, we're looking for an influential design leader who can contribute to our design team as well as our product in building consistent, relevant, and trustworthy experiences. 
Our studios are large, open, spaces where designers, managers, and producers work collaboratively to craft experiences. We are big fans of now virtual sticky notes and design thinking. We take a systems design approach to our work. We partner with top-notch Program Managers, Research Scientists, Data Scientists, Developers, Producers, and Researchers who strategize together on release dates, technological challenges, and customer feedback. Guiding the creation of creative solutions that are relentlessly simple, elegant, and humanistic. 
Our studio is in the Redmond area, and we are open to remote candidates. 
Responsibilities 
You will prove UX concepts at a variety of fidelities, throughout the design process. You will collaborate with PMs, Engineers, Designers, and Researchers to explore and craft experiences utilizing state of the art technology. 
Support design ideas through excellent influencing and communication skills. 
Partner with Program Management and Engineering to drive innovation and incubation of new ideas. 
Guide innovation efforts in collaboration with stakeholders to find designs optimally balancing company, stakeholder, and user needs. 
Contribute to defining user journeys and interaction patterns for new AI and data science-driven technologies and experiences across surfaces. 
Design flows and experiences that are incredibly simple, elegant, humanistic. 
Contribute to high-level strategic decisions with studio leadership and product and executive teams. 
Lead and track cross-functional team design sprints with members outside of the AI + Insights Studio across our Microsoft Design Community. 
Give and solicit feedback from other designers to continually raise our bar for quality, fit and finish. 
Inspire and mentor a diverse team of product designers, producers, content designers, UX researchers, overseeing platform-wide experiences incorporating AI, owning the vision and roadmap from conception until release (and then some). 
Qualifications 
Excellent, highly creative communication and critical thinking skills. 
Bachelor's/Masterâ€™s degree in Computer science, HCI, interaction design, industrial design, communication design, architecture, or equivalent experience. 
3+ years product design experience, ideally in cross-functional teams, and ideally cross-platform products. 
End-to-end design skills (from ideation to prototyping and full production). 
Perfect understanding of design theory (typography, color, grid, etc.). 
Outstanding portfolio showing deep product understanding and craftspersonship, both UI and UX. 
Excellent collaboration skills across disciplines â€“ Program Management, Data Science, AI Research Science, Engineering. 
Able to work independently in a fast-paced environment. 
Has a high level of proficiency designing in Figma. 
Solid understanding of cross-platform design systems and technical frameworks. 
Experience within the Enterprise space is a plus, but not a requirement. 
Recent use and knowledge of Artificial Intelligence, a plus. 
Passion for new, emerging technologies such as AGI, Human Conversational Interfaces, a plus. 
Willingness to adopt new tools and workflows. 
An entrepreneurial spirit with a willingness to frame and define existing/emerging opportunity spaces and success criteria often within ambiguous spaces. 
